The paper discusses the development of a graph-grammar production system to facilitate the modeling of medical decisions. This involves the use of decision-analytic terms and influence-diagram models, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the classification of medical concepts according to semantic types, which is relevant to research in natural language processing and information retrieval (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the graph-grammar production system to aid in decision-making, which is relevant to research in cybersecurity (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
